  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A literature-review activity was conducted to survey published hemolysis correlations and benchmark datasets; findings were compiled into a summary report that informed model-form selection. The review is characterised as providing strong supporting evidence for the hemolysis sub-model and is cited as the primary basis for the output-comparison credibility factor. All 13 credibility factors are addressed; seven carry assessed status with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels, and six are scoped out as not applicable for this COU. Decision: Accepted.",
